full_text: After the meeting was over, I didn't feel better or worse, I mostly felt sorry for the other people in the group. That many years had gone by and most days they only felt like they'd made baby steps past the death of their loved one, mostly parents.
full_text(utf-8): b"After the meeting was over, I didn't feel better or worse, I mostly felt sorry for the other people in the group. That many years had gone by and most days they only felt like they'd made baby steps past the death of their loved one, mostly parents."

full_text: I was able to express myself and that was good, but I can do that in therapy. And it's not that I don't understand their pain, even if their loss was different from my own, but I can't be subject to hear it weekly. Their misery and sadness is too overwhelming.
